 Mpumalanga residents from Low’s Creek, Pienaar, Tonga, Kwaggafontein and Pienaar have embarked on protest action this morning. According to Mpumalanga police spokesman, Brig Leonard Hlathi, they are monitoring these areas and a police official has been dispatched to them to observe and compile a report on the protests. ALSO READ: Teenage murder accused found dead in police cells Police are monitoring the situation. ALSO READ: Retired farmer survives home invasion unharmed Hlathi described the situation as ‘tense’ and said that he would provide more detailed information once he receives the report. The areas mentioned have been hard-hit by protests. Lowvelder will continue providing updates once more information is made available by the South African Police Services.